    "Consistent with previously published methods [92][93][94], we categorized the top 1% of PBS scores as selection outliers, highlighting those that were also differentially expressed (Additional file 1: Tables S9-S10).",
    "Transcriptome experiment for non-cacao Theobroma speciesThe transcriptome experiment followed a split-plot design, where tree was treated as the blocking factor.",
    "Over three consecutive days, we sampled leaves from a single tree for each species (N = 3 trees per species).",
    "From each tree, we took four leaves, two for P. palmivora treatment and two for controls.",
    "These leaves were pooled to create a single biological replicate (N = 3 treatment samples, N = 3 control samples per species)."
